definition.value: A member of the class of benzoyl-CoAs having 4-hydroxy-3-methoxybenzoyl (also known as vanilloyl) as the aroyl group. A potential intermediate of vanillate biosynthesis.
A polypeptide composed of dipeptide Gly-Arg units joined via peptide linkages.
A C-glycosyl compound that is apigenin substituted by a beta-D-glucosyl group and a beta-D-xylosyl group at positions 6 and 8 respectively.
A 3-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is dihydroferulic acid in which the benzylic methylene group has been oxidised to give the corresponding ketone.

A pentacyclic triterpenoid that is 4alpha,14-dimethyl-9beta,19-cyclo-5alpha-ergost-24(28)-ene which is substituted by an oxo group at position 3. It has been isolated from several plant species including Quercus variabilis, Ammocharis coranica, Solanum cernuum and Tinospora crispa.
A 3beta-hydroxy-4alpha-formyl-4beta-methylsteroid that is 24-methylenecycloartanol in which the alpha-methyl substituent at position 4 has been substituted by a hydroxy group.

A 3beta-hydroxy-4alpha-formyl-4beta-methylsteroid that is 24-methylene-9beta-9,19-cyclolanostane-3beta,28-diol in which the hydroxy group at position 28 has been oxidised to give the corresponding aldehyde.
A hydroxy monounsaturated fatty acid anion arising from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of (2E)-4-hydroxynon-2-enoic acid.

A member of the class of cinnamaldehydes that is prop-2-enal in which a hydrogen at position 3 has been replaced by a phenyl group. The configuration of the double bond is not specified; the name "cinnamaldehyde" is widely used to refer to the E (trans) isomer.
A 3beta-sterol that is 5alpha-stigmasta-7,24(28)-dien-3beta-ol which is substituted at the 4alpha position by a hydroxymethyl group and in which the 24(28) double bond has Z configuration.
A 3beta-sterol that is (24Z)-stigmasta-7,24(28)-diene which is substituted at the  3beta and 4alpha positions by hydroxy and formyl groups, respectively.
A polyketide that is deoxyspectinabilin in which the methoxy group at position 2 of the pyranone moiety has been replaced by a hydroxy group.
A glycoside phosphate that is 2-deoxystreptamine which is substituted at position 3S by a glycoside 2alpha phosphate and at position 5R by a glycoside group.
Fully deprotonated form of 5-diphospho-1D-myo-inositol 1,3,4,6-tetrakisphosphate; major species at pH 7.3
